    "To learn the network parameters of an LLM, distributed training algorithms are indispensable and often necessitate the concurrent use of multiple parallel strategies.",
    "• Ability elicitation techniques: Pretrained on vast and varied large-scale corpora, an LLM provides latent possibilities as a flexible instrument for general-purpose activities.",
    "These innate skills, however, might not be readily apparent while the LLM is performing specific activities.",
    "Context-specific learning paradigms or customized task instructions are carefully planned and executed to extract and utilize these potential skills.",
    "• Alignment tuning techniques: LLMs are trained on pretrained corpora to identify and integrate various data features, encompassing high-quality and low-quality information."
  ],
